James de Villiers, News24Police on the scene of the crime. (Le Roux Schoeman, Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A woman was shot on Tuesday morning in an attempted robbery on the corner of Buitengracht and Bloem streets, Cape Town, Western Cape police confirmed.&nbsp;While seated in her vehicle, the woman was approached by a male suspect who demanded her belongings, before shooting her, Western Cape police spokesperson Andr&egrave; Traut said.&nbsp;The incident occurred at 06:22. The woman was taken to a hospital for medical attention.Following the shooting, the man fled the scene and an arrest is yet to be made.&nbsp;Police are investigating a case of attempted murder and robbery, Traut said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.